text: Yeah, it was very interesting and surprising. Because at the time, I was thinking, well, if you're on the comfortable side of SKU, you're probably not a premium collector, you're a premium payer. That was my mentality at the time. And I thought, well, that kind of flies in the face of what all my CTA friends are telling me that, no, no, we're always right SKU, right SKU, we're buying stuff and then our results are right SKU. But the trade result looks right SKU to the client. But after you put the trade on, if you look at the daily or hourly data after that, you're eating a lot of left SKU risk until you finally stop out, which is consistent with my kind of bias in that you don't get paid to be comfortable, you get paid to be uncomfortable. And that means taking the ugly side of SKU risk. That doesn't mean that if you always take the ugly side of SKU risk that you'll make money, you'll probably blow up at some point. But along the path traveled, I guess my point is you don't get paid to make yourself comfortable.
